@startuml
title Weather Monitoring System - UML state machine diagram

[*] --> R1 : [new user]
state R1 <<choice>>

R1 --> L1
L1 : entry/login process
L1 : do/check username and password
L1 : exit/successful login
L1 --> L2
L1 --> E1 : [invalid credentials]

L2 : entry/user is logged in
L2 : do/allow to check weather for current location or another location
L2 : exit/logout

state L3 <<choice>>
L3 : entry/check weather information
L3 : do/update and show selected weather information
L3 : exit/view additional details

L3 --> L4
L4 : entry/valid location entered
L4 : do/allow to choose what to check (temperature, humidity, rainfall, pressure, or dew point)
L4 : exit/end process if new location is not valid

L3 --> E2 : [new location is not valid]
E2 : entry/end process
E2 : do/cannot proceed with the selected location
E2 : exit/logout

@enduml
